race.comment: WROTE TO ARATAKI (3) didn't fire in the spring but she was back at the peak of her powers at Caulfield, winning a race that she has won in the past. This is another that she has previously won and she arrives in the same spot off a better rating. Great chance again. PARADISE CITY (10) might roll across from out wide and keep her company. Up in class but good winner last time and she can give a sight. ETERNAL FLAME (6) was okay off a break. She had only run once in the best part of a year prior so entitled to be rusty but the smart yard have been getting going of late and no shock if she captured some form now. Trip might help SAMANGU (5) find something like her best while TOO DARN DISCREET (4) resumes looking to set up the campaign. Good enough to give her a shot at it but she will be better for the hit out.
